Executive Summary
Led the end-to-end revamp of the PhonePe offer journey, addressing critical market share attrition. By architecting a unified experience spanning discovery, application, benefit disbursal, and post-transaction flows, we transformed a fragmented reward system into a primary growth and retention lever. This initiative drove a 67% increase in user benefit redemption, successfully clawing back 200 bps in market share while simultaneously reducing marketing burn by 32% through algorithmic targeting.

The Challenge: The "Invisible" Offer Problem
Despite running a robust catalog of offers, PhonePe experienced a critical 300 bps drop in market share (slipping from 49% to 46%). The landscape was hyper-competitive: aggressive new entrants like Navi and Super Money were flooding the market with cashbacks, while competitors aggressively utilized homepage pop-ups to become the default receiving app.

User research and Voice of Customer (VOC) data revealed a stark disconnect. Users weren't churning because PhonePe lacked offers; they were churning because the offers were practically invisible.

Core VOC Insights:

"PhonePe isn't giving offers anymore."

"I don't know where to find offers for recharges or bill payments."

"I can't find the reward I was promised."

"There are no offers on my preferred payment instruments."

The fundamental problem was not offer supply, but ubiquitous offer discovery, application transparency, and a frictionless checkout experience.

Strategic Approach & Target Audience
Instead of engaging in a blind price war, we took a targeted, data-driven approach. We identified "switchers"—highly price-sensitive users migrating to competitor platforms for rewards.

To acquire and retain this cohort efficiently, I architected a 'propensity-to-transact' model. This allowed us to intelligently cohort users and target aggressive offers specifically toward these high-flight-risk offer seekers, effectively optimizing our acquisition cost and reducing overall marketing burn by 32%.

Product Solutions & Execution
1. Contextual & Ubiquitous Discovery

Homepage Integration: Brought offer discovery out of hidden menus directly onto the homepage within category tiles.

Smart Placements: Integrated with the recommendation engine to dynamically showcase relevant offers at various high-intent placements throughout the app.

[Insert Design: Homepage category tiles with dynamic offer badges/banners]

2. Revamped Checkout & Application Experience

Supplementary Constraints: Instead of only showing the single offer being automatically applied during checkout, we introduced visibility for other probable offers.

Intelligent Nudging: Implemented real-time checkout nudges prompting users to change their payment instrument or adjust their cart total to unlock a higher-value reward.

Stacks & Sections Logic: Built a robust taxonomy to differentiate "Category-based" and "Instrument-based" offers, allowing users to maximize selectable combinations without breaking unit economics.

[Insert Design: Checkout screen showing nudges, supplementary offers, and Stacks/Sections UI]

3. Closing the Loop: Disbursal & Recall

Post-Transaction Validation: Redesigned the success screen to prominently display the disbursed benefit, featuring direct redirects to the actual reward (closing the cognitive loop on "I didn't get my reward").

Multi-Channel Confirmation: Triggered automated CRM communications confirming benefit disbursal to reinforce brand trust and offer recall.

