Technical Architecture & Scale
To power this dynamic experience without degrading core app performance, we overhauled the backend architecture:

The "Catalogue" Service: Introduced a dedicated service to treat offers as highly marketable, dynamic entities.

Smart Caching: Implemented advanced caching via Catalogue to handle peak homepage traffic loads without relying on heavy database queries.

Latency Guardrails: Maintained strict checkout network latency under 180 ms, ensuring the augmented offer logic didn't slow down the core payment flow.

Business Impact & Key Metrics
Success Metrics (The "Why"):

Market Share: Clawed back 200 bps in market share, directly countering the aggressive tactics of new entrants.

NPS: Jumped from 67% to 71%, with qualitative data citing "ease of finding offers" and "recall of benefits" as the primary drivers.

Product & Support Metrics (The "How"):

Redemption Lift: 67% increase in overall user benefit redemption.

Scratch Card Engagement: Scratch rate improved dramatically from 23% to 76%.

Checkout Conversion: 22% uplift in successful checkouts for offer-applied transactions.

Strategic Instrument Acquisition: 66% increase in users voluntarily switching their default payment option to claim an offer—creating a massive, zero-cost acquisition channel for strategic products like UPI Lite, RuPay Credit Cards, and Co-branded cards.